<p>I am a tinkerer and of course emacs is a perfect vehicle for this mentality.  A prime example of this is my constant evolving modeline.  For many years the default modeline hasn&rsquo;t presented itself as being a problem, but is it optimal for me?, the answer I have now realised is no, and I think I can do better for my use cases.</p>
<figure class="emacs-img"><img src="https://emacs.dyerdwelling.family/ox-hugo/20230902114449-emacs--My-Evolving-Modeline.jpg">
</figure>

<p>So after a period of introspection (regarding emacs! ðŸ™‚) I think I can now define a clear set of criteria for my perfect modeline:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Show the full pathname</p>
<p>By default, emacs displays the buffer name, but during coding sessions, I often prefer to see the full file path, especially since I sometimes work with multiple copies of files with the same name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Clearly indicate when a file has been modified</p>
<p>For when I accidentally insert a &rsquo;n&rsquo; or &lsquo;p&rsquo; character in a buffer (I think you can guess how this happens!) it will be immediately apparent and I will be less likely to break my emacs config.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Have control over the faces</p>
<p>Define my own sizing and colouring for an active and inactive buffer modeline to make clearer my current selected buffer.  Otherwise I will be at the whim of my current theme which may not always be optimal.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Efficient information display</p>
<p>Fit as much information in a compact manner as possible, I don&rsquo;t want to be hunting around for buffer information, for example the column number and major modes should always be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Version control menu should be available</p>
<p>I frequently use git/magit for version control and prefer to keep the menu bar disabled. This choice sometimes leads me to search for built-in VC (Version Control) commands within emacs. For instance, registering a new file in magit can be tricky since untracked files seem to only display top-level directories unless a subdirectory file has been registered. To include all files in a directory, I rely on vc-register, but I don&rsquo;t always remember the key chord. Therefore, having a VC menu in the mode line is immensely helpful.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Simplicity</p>
<p>This includes keeping the modeline elisp definition as simple as possible for easier maintainability / transparency and never allowing extra items to creep in like email or miscellaneous information.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Given all this I have come up with the following:</p>
