</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>     mode-line-modes
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>     )
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>  )
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>(setq mode-line-compact <span style="color:#66d9ef">t</span>)
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>I have tried to use the built-in modeline variables where possible and use <code>mode-line-compact</code> which replaces repeating spaces with a single space.</p>
<p>I found the best way to indicate a modified file and for it to clearly stand out on the modeline is by colour and string length, but I still wanted to keep the asterisk convention as this is quite common.</p>
<p>I decided to subtly change the size of the active and inactive modeline for extra emphasis and this can be massively exaggerated to taste.</p>